IDM wins $ 21 mln contract for dam project . IDM Environmental Corp said Tuesday it and its joint venture partner , Sudhakar Engineering , were contracted to perform drilling and grouting on California ' s East Dam Reservoir project . The value of the contract is about $ 21 million , the company said . The company said it expects to book a portion of this contract in its fourth quarter financial results . " This project should have a material impact on our 1997 sales and earnings , " said Frank Falco , IDM ' s board chairman . Work by the joint venture is slated to begin in early December , with completion expected by March 1998 , IDM said . 
